I believe Amber heard was one such case, her stories portraying herself as a victim were believed to quickly and now there is evidence suggesting she is also an abuser, so instead of acknowledging the mistake, the media is steering into the skid and trying to turn the story back in her and their favour, most see can see through the lies now. 
Is there a fear that by acknowledging this woman isnt as innocent as she portrays herself that it may undo some of the good of the metoo movement? As it would potentially shine a light on all woman who have made accusations against men, maybe unravelling some good in the process? The answer is probably yes but it needs to be done. Otherwise woman like Amber will take advantage of the situation and men like Johnny depp will suffer unfairly. (of note, i don't think Johnny depp is always perfect, he has a drug and alcohol problem but i don't think he should lose his job and be vilified in the media and i don't belive he is a wife beater) Amber and Johnny both behaved poorly throughout their toxic relationship but it appears Amber may have been the aggressor, Amber shouldn't get a pass because she's a woman, despite Johnny poor behaviour.
